I certainly must agree that compromise is a good idea.  I also think
it will be a fine if UUCP is administerred by its own inmates.

Therefore, when some responsible people who are trying to administer
the UUCP domain ask for suggestions, I am inclinded to help, rather
than suggest that they go off in some whole new direction, like
reconsider using long names because they are OK in some other domains.

Given that the relevant geographical area identifiers for UUCP are
more likely to be AREA CODES (because UUCP uses DDD connections),
perhaps the subdoamains of UUCP could be something like uu212 for New
York, etc.  To me, this would provide highly intuitive subdomains, and
provide reasonably accurate and fine grained (toll-wise) table lookup
keys for picking an "optimuim" gateway for any given UUCP address.

I also note that such subdomain names would be very consistent and of
uniform 5 character length.

Best - Stef

